Detailed Description

VQE-C CLI command definition utilizing vqec_cli. VQEC uses CLI commands for providing commands for test, debug and diagnostics via telnet.

#define VQEC_DP_IPC_GET_DEBUG_FLAG ( name,
flag   ) 

Value:

({                                                                  \
        *flag = FALSE;                                                  \
        (void)vqec_dp_debug_flag_get(name, flag);                       \
        *flag;                                                          \
    })

#define VQEC_MAXCMDLEN   256

#define VQEC_PARSE_ADDR_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (!strncmp(_name, param_name, ARG_STRLEN)) {              \
        temp_addr.s_addr = inet_addr(param_value);              \
        cfg->_field = temp_addr;                                \
        inet_ntop(AF_INET, &cfg->_field, tmp, INET_ADDRSTRLEN); \
        /* dotted-decimal format check */                       \
        if (strncmp(param_value, tmp, INET_ADDRSTRLEN)) {       \
            return FALSE;                                       \
        }                                                       \
    } else

#define VQEC_PARSE_ENABLE_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (!strncmp(_name, param_name, ARG_STRLEN)) {      \
        cfg->_field = TRUE;                             \
    } else

#define VQEC_PARSE_INT_PARAM ( _name,
_field,
_type   ) 

Value:

if (!strncmp(_name, param_name, ARG_STRLEN)) {      \
        cfg->_field = (_type)atol(param_value);         \
        /* Overflow check (cast may not succeed) */     \
        if (cfg->_field != atol(param_value)) {         \
            return FALSE;                               \
        }                                               \
    } else

#define VQEC_PARSE_PORT_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (!strncmp(_name, param_name, ARG_STRLEN)) {          \
        cfg->_field = htons((uint16_t)atoi(param_value));   \
        if (ntohs(cfg->_field) != atol(param_value)) {      \
            return FALSE;                                   \
        }                                                   \
    } else

#define VQEC_PARSE_XRENABLE_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (!strncmp(_name, param_name, ARG_STRLEN)) {      \
        cfg->_field = VQEC_RTCP_XR_RLE_ENABLE;          \
    } else

#define VQEC_PARSE_XRFLAGS_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (!strncmp(_name, param_name, ARG_STRLEN)) {      \
        if (strstr(param_value, "loss")) {              \
            cfg->_field |= VQEC_RTCP_XR_STAT_LOSS;      \
        }                                               \
        if (strstr(param_value, "dup")) {               \
            cfg->_field |= VQEC_RTCP_XR_STAT_DUP;       \
        }                                               \
        if (strstr(param_value, "jitt")) {              \
            cfg->_field |= VQEC_RTCP_XR_STAT_JITT;      \
        }                                               \
    } else

#define VQEC_PRINT_ADDR_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

fprintf(f, "%s %s ", _name,              \
            inet_ntop(AF_INET, &cfg->_field, \
                      tmp, INET_ADDRSTRLEN))

#define VQEC_PRINT_ENABLE_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (cfg->_field) {                          \
        fprintf(f, "%s", _name);                \
    }                                           \
    fprintf(f, " ")

#define VQEC_PRINT_INT_PARAM ( _name,
_field,
_format   )     fprintf(f, "%s " _format " ", _name, cfg->_field)

#define VQEC_PRINT_PORT_PARAM ( _name,
_field   )     fprintf(f, "%s %hu ", _name, ntohs(cfg->_field))

#define VQEC_PRINT_XRENABLE_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (cfg->_field != VQEC_RTCP_XR_RLE_UNSPECIFIED) {  \
        fprintf(f, "%s", _name);                        \
    }                                                   \
    fprintf(f, " ")

#define VQEC_PRINT_XRFLAGS_PARAM ( _name,
_field   ) 

Value:

if (cfg->_field) {                          \
        fprintf(f, "%s ", _name);               \
    }                                           \
    if (cfg->_field & VQEC_RTCP_XR_STAT_LOSS) { \
        fprintf(f, "loss");                     \
    }                                           \
    if (cfg->_field & VQEC_RTCP_XR_STAT_DUP) {  \
        fprintf(f, ",dup");                     \
    }                                           \
    if (cfg->_field & VQEC_RTCP_XR_STAT_JITT) { \
        fprintf(f, ",jitt");                    \
    }                                           \
    fprintf(f, " ")

#define VQEC_PRIVILEGE_INIT_ONLY   100

static void fastFillStartHandler ( int32_t  context_id,
vqec_ifclient_fastfill_params_t *  params 
) [static]

The following three functions are used to test VQE-C fast fill feature from vqec CLI "tuner bind", without the STB.

Please note, these functions are only for testing purpose. If you are in a STB which has fast fill feature integrated, doing "tuner bind" from CLI does not provide you the full functionalities of fast fill. It only streams out packets from VQE-C in a faster rate.

static void* vqec_cli_loop_thread ( void *  arg  )  [static]

int vqec_cli_loop_wrapper ( uint16_t  cli_port,
in_addr_t  cli_if_addr 
)

Creates a telnet socket listening to the <cli_port> and then loops waiting to receive cli commands on that port. Only VQEC_CLI_CLIENT_MAX clients are accepted.

Parameters:
[in] cli_port - specifies telnet port for the cli. note specifying a cli_port of zero does not start a telnet server.
[in] cli_if_addr - specifies the interface address to bind the telnet server to. note specifying a cli_if_addr of zero binds the server to listen on all interfaces.
Returns:
0 if the loop exits normally, 1 if the loop exited because the telnet server failed to start.
CLI telnet session. See vqec_cli_loop.

Callback function to display show tech-support information.

The information dumped is equivalent to what would be seen if a user were to log into the VQE-C CLI and issue the following commands: show system-config show tuner all detail show channel show counters show dp counters show update show drop show error-repair show fec show rcc show fast-fill show nat show pak-pool show stream-output show ipc show proxy-igmp

param[in] cli struct cli_def * - the handle of the cli structure. param[in] command char * - the entire command which was entered. This is after command expansion. param[in]argv char ** - the list of arguments entered param[in]argc int - the number of arguments entered

Returns:
vqec_error_t Returns VQEC_OK if the API was successfully executed.
